Spinoecia

—Poulsen: 110–11 (part);

First antenna . The limb in most species has no a dorsal seta, rarely with a rudimentary (in
P. porrecta in Drapun & Smith 2012
) or developed seta (in
P. crassispina in Chen & Lin 1987
). Seta-e is bare or armed with small, medium-length or long, anterior, fine filaments proximally. Setae-a–d at most are shorter than the shaft of the limb.

Sixth limb . The coxale has two long, but unequal plumose setae. The basale bears five ventral, long, plumose setae (only four setae are in
P. porrecta in Poulsen 1973
) and without or with one lateral short or long seta (plumose or bare).
